@node "Template" "Template"

 Name Of Software & Version

  ->name of software (i.e. Heddley)

 Exact Filename / Size (in bytes if possible) / AmiNet Directory

  ->Just as above asks (i.e. getid226.lha 14K comm/bbs)

 Brief Description

  ->Give a breif description about the program.

 Author / Copyright Information

  ->All the info about the author provided by the author (email, web,
  ->usmail, irc, etc).

 ShareWare Fee

  ->Give the amount of any fees required.  Label "Freeware" if none.

 Limitations for Demo (if any)

  ->Some software has limitions; list them here if any.

 Hardware /  Software Requirements

  ->Tell of any software or hardware requirements such as
  ->WB 3.0, AGA, MUI, etc.

 Installation

  ->Mark an X in the appropriate box.

    ( ) Easy ( ) Medium ( ) Hard ( ) C= Installer

 Documentation

  ->How well is the program documented?

 Known Bugs

  ->Are there any known bugs?  Some you found?

 Review Begins

  ->The largest part of your review.  Write all your likes
  ->dislikes and what the program can do.  Try to list key
  ->features and, if a game, fun factors.  Cover every aspect that is
  ->important to the use of the software.  Get as detailed as you like.

 Writer's Info

  ->Put your name and any other info you want (short bio?), such as your
  ->email/usmail address or web page.
@endnode

@node "ASokoban" "ASokoban"

 @{fg shine}Name Of Software @{fg text}

  ASokoban V2.4

 @{fg shine}Archive Name, Size, and Directory on Aminet@{fg text}

  ASokoban24.lha, 43K, game/think

 @{fg shine}Brief Description@{fg text}

  This is a cool little Workbench game where you move a pair of eyes through
  a series of mazes pushing bags of money into a "safe".

 @{fg shine}Author Information@{fg text}

  Panagiotis Christias
  e-mail: d93-hyo@nada.kth.se
  s-mail: Sandkullsvägen 16, 163 57 Spånga, Sweden
  Copyright © 1993 Panagiotis Christias, Copyright © 1995 Lorens Younes.

 @{fg shine}ShareWare/PD Fee@{fg text}

  Freeware

 @{fg shine}Hardware Software Requirements@{fg text}

  ASokoban will run on any Amiga with WB 2.0 or higher.

 @{fg shine}Installation@{fg text}

    ( ) Easy ( ) Medium ( ) Hard (X) C= Installer

 @{fg shine}Documentation@{fg text}

  The documentation is short, simple and to the point.

 @{fg shine}Review Begins@{fg text}

  Well yet another fun game to play on the workbench.  This game uses very
  simple graphics, cursor control and a pair of eyes to keep you entertained
  while you're letting the day slip by...  This game has lots of levels.  I
  solved the first three easily and kept moving on into the other levels
  slower and slower.  It supports the following catalogs:

                        English
                        Danish
                        Finnish
                        German
                        Norwegian
                        Polish

  The author is working on a level editor.  It keeps track of high scores,
  and it looks great on a high resolution Workbench.

